text.tspan: - Other than Wi-Fi and VPN, every menu item toggles the function
- Night light's dual state is on and paused
- Battery menu item is removed (battery percentage is shown in the top bar when the menu is open)
- Power off becomes a sub-menu, which contains suspend
- User sub-menu is moved to the bottom and is permanently displayed
- Confirmation dialogs for power off/restart are only shown when there are active inhibits
- Expose a suspend action without the need to hold down a modifier key
- Resolve awkward user menu - tiny image, awkward placement
- Avoid sub-menus with only one action in them

flowRoot.flowPara: Applications are busy or have unsaved work.

text.tspan: - Two disclosure patterns in the system menu could feel odd; there are various options for how it could be presented though
- It needs to be obvious how to close the user and power off sub-menus
- Need to test whether users will understand that the menu items toggle
- It would be good for the menu to communicate when updates are available. Perhaps the power icon could change in this situation.
- Perhaps confirmation dialogs are needed for restart and install updates? - it can take a while, and it's a single click from Software

flowRoot.flowPara: The system will power off in 60 seconds.

text.tspan: - Avoid disappearing sub-menus. Example: turning off location services, airplane mode
- Don't confuse temporary disable with permanent disable
- Don't show a sub-menu for location services
- Could continue to only show night light when it's active, or could show it permanently
- Show a clear hint that clicking the menu item for screen sharing and recording cancels, like
Possible elaboration: change logic for when sub-menus are shown
